These are very important ways to work with the project:

 - Only use existing shadcn components, do not create your own or modify them unless explicity asked to.
 - Create reusable components each in their own files. Roughly speaking, no one file should be more than 50 LOC (except if for a reason)
 - Look for and use existing components before pulling in anything new. The goal is simple reusablility.
 - Prefer dead simple code of elegant code. Complexity is the enemy.

These are very important ways to structure the project:

 - The mobile experience is very important, pay special attention to it. UI principles for mobile design should apply here (appropiately spaced and sized elements, using `touch-action: manipulation;` to remove touch delay, etc).